The paper deals with object detection in autonomous driving using visual data, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) categories. The proposed method involves using convolutional neural networks, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the KITTI benchmark, which is a well-known benchmark in computer vision and has a dedicated conference (CVPR), making cs.CVPR a likely category as well.
